From: stuff overlay maintainer
Subject: Build against CGAL >= 6.0

CGAL 6.0 changed Surface_mesh::add_property_map / property_map to return
std::optional<Property_map> instead of std::pair<Property_map, bool>.
A small access_pmap() helper unwraps both forms so the source still
compiles against older CGAL too. CGAL 6.1 then removed the AABB_traits
class template (renamed to AABB_traits_3 in 6.0; the legacy alias is
gone in 6.1), so the AABB tree typedef has to be updated explicitly.

--- a/src/libslic3r/CutSurface.cpp
+++ b/src/libslic3r/CutSurface.cpp
@@ -1,5 +1,13 @@
 #include "CutSurface.hpp"
 
+template <typename T>
+auto access_pmap(std::optional<T> opt) -> T {
+    return opt.value();
+}
+
+template <typename Pair>
+auto access_pmap(Pair pair) { return pair.first; }
+
